history.content:
We at Leetcode 101 have received a lot of inquiries about joining our course recently. While enrollment is now closed due to capacity issues, we really appreciate your interest, and we wish we were able to accommodate more people at this time. We will also not be having a waitlist due to accidental overenrollment. The Academic Guide mentioned that we would have a course size of 500, but due to Zoom limitations and a lean course staff, we will not be able to accommodate more than the currently enrolled 284. We recognize that many people feel it unfair our enrollment closed well before the semester has  begun. However, when we started this DeCal, we did not realize how many people would want to join a memey class focused on gaming the system (and run by two jokey codemonkeys), so we advertised early on the EECS 101 Piazza. In the future, we will try to make enrollment more equitable towards those who do not doomscroll here. Our website is up at leetcode101.com if you'd like to follow along with recordings and homeworks posted weekly. If you'd like to join in the fall, we recommend following the EECS 101 Piazza, and we will also be sure to advertise on other platforms (such as Facebook and Reddit) in a more reasonable time frame that is closer to the start of the semester.

Wishing you a successful semester and happy recruiting, 

The Leetcode Decal Team
